<title>USA: IPO FILING - Dr Solomon's Group Plc.</title>
<headline>IPO FILING - Dr Solomon's Group Plc.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1996-11-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Company Name	    Dr Solomon's Group PLC</p>
<p>Stock symbol			SOLLY.O</p>
<p>Estimated price range	   $15-$17 per ADS</p>
<p>Total American depositary</p>
<p>    shares to be offered	5.7 million</p>
<p>ADSs offered by company	 3.99 million</p>
<p>ADSS offered by shareholders  1.71 million Ordinary shrs outstanding</p>
<p>    after IPO		     55.235 million</p>
<p>Lead underwriter    Goldman, Sachs &amp; Co</p>
<p>Underwriters over-allotment  855,000 shrs Business: Buckinghamshire, England,-based company develops, markets and supports anti-virus software programs for personal computers and PC networks. Use of Proceeds: To repay or redeem obligations incurred by company in connection with management buyout of S&amp;S International, the former parent of the company, and for general corporate purposes. Such purposes include expansion of North American sales, increased investment in research and development, expansion of production capacity, development of improved management information systems and possible acqusitions.</p>
</text>
